Angola May Waive Last $400 Million of $1.4 Billion IMF Loan, O Pais Says

-- B y   C a n d i d o   M e n d e s
-- 
2011-05-23T11:03:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/angola-may-waive-last-400-million-of-1-4-billion-imf-loan-o-pais-says.html
Angola  will decide in the next few
days whether to take the final $400 million of a $1.4 billion
loan from the  International Monetary Fund , O Pais reported,
without saying where it got the information.  A group from the IMF is expected in the southern African
nation tomorrow to conduct a review of the economy, the Luanda-
based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Candido Mendes in Luanda at 
 cmendes6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  